definition.value: A dipeptide formed from L-isoleucine and L-proline residues.

An S-hydrocarbyl-L-cysteine that is L-cysteine in which the  hydrogen attached to the sulphur is replaced by a prop-2-enyl group. It commonly occurs in garlic and has been found to exhibit antineoplastic activity.
A dipeptide formed from L-isoleucine and L-serine residues.
A thiourea with a prop-2-enyl group attached to one of the amines.
A dipeptide formed from L-isoleucine and L-tryptophan residues.
A glycerophosphoinositol phosphate that is 1-archaetidyl-1D-myo-inositol bearing an additional phospho substituent at position 3.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-tetracosapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-tetracosapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid that is acrylic acid with substituents 4-methoxyphenyl at position 2 and 6-methylpyridin-2-yl at position 3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-tetracosahexaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-tetracosatetraenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A glycerophosphoinositol that is 1-D-myo-inositol substituted at position 1 by an archaetidyl group.
An organic phosphonate that is adenosine having a [(3S)-3-amino-4-carboxy-2-oxobutyl](hydroxy)phosphoryl group attached at position 5'.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (9Z,12Z)-3-oxolinoleic acid.

A member of the class of biotins that is biotin sulfoxide with a sulfone group replacing the sulfoxide.

A polyprenyl phospho polysaccharide that consists of the polysaccharide 3-O-phospho-[2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->]n-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcNAc linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.
A polyprenyl phospho carbohydrate in which the carbohydrate portion is any polysaccharide.
An acylcholine with an acyl group that is hexanoyl.

A polyprenyl phospho polysaccharide that consists of the polysaccharide 3-O-methylphospho-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)]n-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcNAc linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.

A polyprenyl phospho polysaccharide that consists of the polysaccharide alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)]n-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcNAc linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.
An N-acylglycine that has octanoyl as the acyl group.
A dihydroceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as (9Z)-octadecenoyl (oleoyl).
An amino acid amide that is methylglycinamide with an acetyl group substituent on the amino group.
A cholesterol ester in which the acyl group is specified as  (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl.
A cholesterol ester in which the acyl group contains 22 carbons in total and 6 double bonds.
An S-substituted L-cysteine where the S-substituent is specified as (2-hydroxyethyl)sulfane.
An aldonolactone obtained by formal oxidation of the anomeric position of any aldopyranose.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of erucic acid.
An acylcholine obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of decanoic acid with the hydroxy group of choline.

A germacrane sesquiterpenoid in which the 10-membered ring contains one E- and one Z- double bond and is fused to a 3-methylenedihydrofuran-2(3H)-one moiety. It has been isolated from Artemesia arbuscala, Anthemis altissima and Tanacetum vulgare.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (11Z,14Z)-3-oxoicosa-11,14-dienoic acid.
A secondary aliphatic amine with two undecyl groups
A fluoroamino acid that is lysine with a difluoromethyl group at position 2.
A non-proteinogenic amino-acid derivative that is norvaline (2-aminopentanoic acid) in which a hydrogen at position 3 is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A germacrane sesquiterpenoid found in Tanacetum vulgare, Anthemis altissima and Anthemis melanolepsis that is tatridin A in which the double bond at position 9-10 has migrated to position 10-14.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (11Z,14Z,17Z)-3-oxoicosatrienoic acid.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 2-hydroxypalmitoyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 2-hydroxystearoyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 2-hydroxybehenoyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 2-hydroxytetracosanoyl-CoA.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (3S)-3-methyl-2-oxo-3-phenylpropanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A dipeptide formed from glycine and L-methionine residues.
An O-acylcarnitine having 11-carboxyundecanoyl as the acyl substituent.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is pyruvic acid in which two of the methyl hydrogens are substituted by phenyl and methyl groups (the S-enantiomer).
A member of the class of guanidines that consists of hexanoic acid substituted by a guanidino group at position 6.
A biphenylyltetrazole that is losartan with the hydroxymethyl group at position 5 on the imidazole ring replaced with a carboxylic acid.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (11Z)-eicosenoic acid.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (13Z)-3-oxodocosenoic acid.
A C24:1-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (15Z)-tetracosenoyl-CoA.
